  "response_text": "For a healthy and celebratory dinner, consider preparing a Grilled Lemon Herb Salmon with Quinoa and Roasted Vegetables. Here’s a complete menu:\n\n### Main Dish: Grilled Lemon Herb Salmon\n**Ingredients:**\n- Salmon fillets\n- Fresh lemon juice and zest\n- Olive oil\n- Fresh herbs (such as dill, parsley, and oregano)\n- Garlic, minced\n- Salt and pepper\n\n**Instructions:**\n1. In a bowl, mix lemon juice, lemon zest, olive oil, minced garlic, chopped herbs, salt, and pepper.\n2. Marinate the salmon fillets in the mixture for at least 30 minutes.\n3. Preheat the grill or oven to medium-high heat.\n4. Grill the salmon for about 6-8 minutes on each side or until cooked through and flaky.\n\n### Side Dish: Quinoa Salad\n**Ingredients:**\n- Quinoa (1 cup)\n- Vegetable broth or water (2 cups)\n- Cherry tomatoes, halved\n- Cucumber, diced\n- Red onion, finely chopped\n- Bell peppers, diced\n- Fresh parsley or cilantro\n- Olive oil\n- Lemon juice\n- Salt and pepper\n\n**Instructions:**\n1. Rinse the quinoa under cold water. Cook it in vegetable broth or water according to package instructions.\n2. In a large bowl, combine the cooked quinoa, cherry tomatoes, cucumber, red onion, bell peppers, and herbs.\n3. Drizzle with olive oil and lemon juice, then season with salt and pepper to taste. Toss gently to combine.\n\n### Side Dish: Roasted Seasonal Vegetables\n**Ingredients:**\n- A mix of seasonal vegetables (such as zucchini, bell peppers, carrots, and Brussels sprouts)\n- Olive oil\n- Fresh herbs (such as thyme or rosemary)\n- Salt and pepper\n\n**Instructions:**\n1. Preheat the oven to 400°F (200°C).\n2. Chop the vegetables into even-sized pieces and toss them with olive oil, herbs, salt, and pepper.\n3. Spread them in a single layer on a baking sheet and roast for 20-25 minutes, or until tender and caramelized.\n\n### Dessert: Greek Yogurt Parfait\n**Ingredients:**\n- Greek yogurt (plain or flavored)\n- Fresh berries (strawberries, blueberries, raspberries)\n- Granola or nuts for topping\n- Honey or maple syrup (optional)\n\n**Instructions:**\n1. In a glass or bowl, layer Greek yogurt, fresh berries, and granola or nuts.\n2. Drizzle with honey or maple syrup if desired for added sweetness.\n\n### Beverage: Sparkling Water with Fresh Citrus\nServe sparkling water infused with slices of lemon, lime, or orange for a refreshing, festive drink.\n\nThis dinner is not only healthy but also colorful and festive, perfect for a celebration! Enjoy!",
